---
title: Moveswap
hidden: false
---
The **Moveswap** is one of the most famous glitches in *Dark Souls* . It allows the player to "swap" the moveset of one weapon onto another. This effectively lets you use the attack animations of a fast weapon while wielding a much heavier, more powerful one.

The most common application involves using the [**Estoc**](http://darksouls.wikidot.com/estoc) or **Rapier** as the "source" weapon. By performing the glitch, you can apply their high-speed running , rolling and backstep attacks to heavy-hitting weapons like the [**Black Knight Halberd**](http://darksouls.wikidot.com/black-knight-halberd) **(BKH)**, [**Dragon Tooth**](http://darksouls.wikidot.com/dragon-tooth)**..**.

Because the [**Bow**](http://darksouls.wikidot.com/bows) is the only weapon type that can be **two-handed in the left hand**, it can be used to trick the game's logic. By performing specific actions, players can force the game to **two-hand a weapon of their choice** in the left hand, even if that weapon normally wouldn't allow it.

This results in a massive increase in DPS (Damage Per Second), as you are hitting with the strength of a giant hammer at the speed of a thrusting sword.

It is **highly recommended to** [**downpatch**](/ds1remaster/downpatch) your game to make the Moveswap significantly easier.

This Glitch was discovered by **Eloise** in august 2024 : [https://youtu.be/LO_cbxkc72k](https://youtu.be/LO_cbxkc72k)

